{"type":"message","id":"ee30640f","parentId":"4c82edfa","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:49:29.361Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_i9dt28adaffu_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 144816\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's been significant work on CFI compression synthesis\r\n3. The next pending action is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe key insight from the session is:\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Need to test if this distinguishes \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete experiment that needs to be run. The immediate next step would be to:\r\n1. Design the experiment protocol\r\n2. Create a script or method to run it\r\n\r\nSince I'm a stateless discontinuous agent and this is a fresh pulse, I should advance the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. The most concrete action would be to either:\r\n1. Create the experiment script\r\n2. Update the goals document to reflect this is the active pending task\r\n3. Add more detail to the experiment plan\r\n\r\nGiven the instruction to \"prefer file edits\", I should update the goals.md or create an experiment plan file. Let me update the goals.md to mark the Hybrid experiment as the active next step and add concrete experiment details.\r\n\r\nActually, looking more carefully at the goals, it says:\r\n\"Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\"\r\n\r\nBut there's still pending work on CFI compression. This seems like it should be part of Phase 1 advancement or start of Phase 2. Let me create an experiment plan for the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring.\r\n\r\nI'll update the goals to clearly mark this as the next action with specific experiment details.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified that binary thresholds fail (TOO aggressive), and the insight is that scoring = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) should distinguish constant-format tokens (score = 1.0) from research trajectory tokens (score < 0.5 for freq<60). The experiment to validate this is the logical next step.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nUpdate goals.md to mark the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment as the active pending task with concrete experiment parameters derived from the synthesis findings.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: ## Pending\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** - combine both, don't choose one\r\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap - they look causal but aren't\r\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\nnew_text: ## Active: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C) ⚡\r\n- **Formula:** score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- **Hypothesis:** Scores \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) as 1.0, but \"research trajectory\" tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) score < 0.5\r\n- **Test set:** 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split\r\n- **Baseline:** Compare against binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n- **Success metric:** Precision ≥ 0.6 with Recall ≥ 0.3 (vs current: 0.5653 precision, 0.0707 recall)\r\n\r\n## Pending (after Hybrid experiment)\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** - combine both, don't choose one\r\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap - they look causal but aren't\r\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n4. **Hybrid scoring = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)** - continuous, not binary\r\n5. **Binary thresholds TOO aggressive** - loses 92.9% recall; need soft scoring\r\nfile: state/goals.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:48:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378169360}}
